      "date": "2013-12-02 20:05:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI'm not against adding checks on the client side, but it seems like this indicates a problem somewhere else in the code?  It would seem to me that op_namelen should be set correctly to begin with?  Adding extra calls to strnlen() seems like a workaround for op_namelen being set incorrectly when op_name is first assigned.",
